The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Predicted sales increase of 15\%
&nbsp;
* Predicted increase in the balance sheet accounts of 15\%

Now, let us compute the increase in the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Sales}&=\text{Sales}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$38,000}\times{15\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$5,700}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the sales amounts to \$5,700.**

Now, let us compute the projected sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Sales}&=\text{Sales}+\text{Increase in Sales}\\[12pt]
&={\$38,000}+{\$5,700}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$43,700}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected sales is \$43,700.**

Now, let us compute the increase in the cost:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Cost}&=\text{Cost}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$32,600}\times{15\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$4,890}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the cost amounts to \$4,890.**

Now, let us compute the projected cost:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Cost}&=\text{Cost}+\text{Increase in Cost}\\[12pt]
&={\$32,600}+{\$4,890}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$37,490}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected cost is \$37,490.**

Now, let us compute the projected net income:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Net Income}&=\text{Sales}-\text{Cost}\\[12pt]
&={\$43,700}-{\$37,490}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$6,210}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected net income is \$6,210.**

Now, let us compute the increase in the assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Assets}&=\text{Assets}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$27,300}\times{15\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$4,095}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the assets amounts to \$4,095.**

Now, let us compute the projected assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Assets}&=\text{Assets}+\text{Increase in Assets}\\[12pt]
&={\$27,300}+{\$4,095}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$31,395}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected assets is \$31,395.**

Now, let us compute the increase in the debt:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Debt}&=\text{Debt}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$6,700}\times{15\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$1,005}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the debt amounts to \$1,005.**

Now, let us compute the projected debt:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Debt}&=\text{Debt}+\text{Increase in Debt}\\[12pt]
&={\$6,700}+{\$1,005}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$7,705}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected debt is \$7,705.**

Now, let us compute the increase in the equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Equity}&=\text{Equity}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$20,600}\times{15\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$3,090}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the equity amounts to \$3,090.**

Now, let us compute the projected equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Equity}&=\text{Equity}+\text{Increase in Equity}\\[12pt]
&={\$20,600}+{\$3,090}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$23,690}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected equity is \$23,690.**

Now, let us compute the total debt and equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Debt and Equity}&=\text{Debt}+\text{Equity}\\[12pt]
&={\$7,705}+{\$23,690}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$31,395}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The total debt and equity is \$31,395.**

Based on the initial balance sheet prepared, the estimated increase in equity is only \$3,090 while the increase in net income is \$6,210. The difference in the amounts is computed as follows:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Difference}&=\text{Net Income}-\text{Increase in Equity}\\[12pt]
&={\$6,210}-{\$3,090}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$3,120}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The difference in the net income and the increase in equity is \$3,120.**
